</taxonomicName>
but hymenium hyaline, ascospores shorter, 15–24 × 6–9 µm vs. 20–26 × 6–8 µm, rarely submuriform, and growing on 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E381A735994EFB1CD7BB0424499D" authorityName="G.De Notaris" authorityYear="1846" box="[1204,1285,388,414]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Caliciaceae" genus="Buellia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Caliciales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724410A735994EFB1CD7BB0424499D" box="[1204,1285,388,414]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Buellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E381A735994EFA9AD7BA04AA499D" authorityName="P.M.Jorg., L.Lindblom, Wedin &amp; S.Ekman" authorityYear="2014" box="[1330,1419,389,414]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pannariaceae" genus="Nevesia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Peltigerales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724410A735994EFA9AD7BA04AA499D" box="[1330,1419,389,414]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Nevesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
